{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3448153,"name":"","username":"Aiden_m","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/c67d28/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-11-15T22:24:30.188Z","cooked":"

During assembly of our swerve XS modules two to the contact bearings got put in upside down. This resulted in a bunch of gunk from the carpet and overall wear getting inside the bearings. Our first thought of cleaning them is to soak them in degreaser then apply a bunch of red and tacky grease to re grease them. Is there a better way of cleaning and re greasing the bearings?

Nah, that’s perfect. Be careful with the degreaser, the water based types can cause corrosion especially if you over-dilute them. May need a toothbrush to scrub out the old grease, give them a few washes.

As great as it seems, don’t toss them in an ultrasonic cleaner. Can cause weird damage on the ground surfaces.

troy_dietz:

Can cause weird damage on the ground surfaces.

Can you elaborate?

i.e. What was the cleaning solution? Was it heated? What make/model of ultrasonic cleaner was used (home jewelry cleaner or laboratory grade)? Was this personal experience? What was the damage? What condition was the bearing before cleaning? etc.
Thanks.
